    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"public safety\" can be such a huge, vague term. it feels like governments could just use that excuse to override any belief they don't like. shouldn't the priority be protecting the individual's right to live by their conscience? it seems like if the state can just decide what counts as \"public good\" to override religion, then religious freedom isn't actually a real right anymore, is it?",
